title: Man Stabbed To Death In Apparent Dispute Over Unpaid Rent « CBS New York
text:
Man Stabbed To Death In Apparent Dispute Over Unpaid Rent February 22, 2017 9:59 PM Filed Under: Bronx , NYPD 
NEW YORK (CBSNewYork) — Police are questioning a Bronx man in connection to a fatal stabbing Wednesday evening. 
Authorities say around 7:00 pm a 44-year-old male was stabbed multiple times throughout the body by another 51-year-old man at 1001 Logan Avenue. 
The victim was rushed to NYC Health + Hospitals/Jacobi where he was pronounced dead. 
Neighbors tell CBS2 the suspect — who is the landlord of the property — is a nice man that must have reached a breaking point, citing recent complaints that the 41-year-old — a tenant in the property — had not been paying rent. 
Stick with CBSNewYork for more on this developing story.
